page_context[1]:
  - title: "Runink FACE"
    permalink: "https://runink.org/products/face/"
    date: "0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"
    category: "products"
    description: "The operational immune system. Real-time visibility, active enforcement, and autonomous repair."
    content: " The Team That Never Sleeps. Stop treating symptoms. Deploy automated systems that find lost money, block bad orders, and fix problems while you sleep. It\u0026rsquo;s not software. It\u0026rsquo;s an automated workforce. Meet Your New System Don't Manage Data. Manage Outcomes. Dashboards don't pay the bills. Actions do. Runink isn't a tool for looking at charts. It's a set of engines that do the work for you. Executive Summary: Key Takeaways ✓ Autonomous Action Execution: Shift from passive dashboards to active operations. The FACE auto-files claims and orchestrates orders, reducing manual operational drag by up to 60%. ✓ Predictive Margin Protection: Utilizing the Hypothesis Lab, logistics operators can simulate pricing changes and routing rules, reliably predicting margin impacts before executing risky operational shifts. ✓ Automated Guardrail Enforcement: The Rules Studio dynamically codifies standard operating procedures, instantly blocking anomalies like duplicate POs or unverified vendor requests, mitigating compliance risk. 1. Rules Studio Teach It Once. You know how to run your business. The problem is, you can't be everywhere at once. Rules Studio lets you teach the system your \\\"Best Practices\\\" one time, and it remembers them forever. Teach it to recover revenue: \\\"If a shipment sits for 7 days, chase the carrier.\\\"\nTeach it to block risk: \\\"If a duplicate order comes in, stop it.\\\" ✓ Performance: See how much money your rules saved you. ✓ Detail View: Check exactly why a rule fired. ✓ Deploy: Push new rules instantly. 2. Operations Actionable Twins Work Gets Done. This isn't a chat bot. It's a command center. Your automated operations sit here, waiting for your approval to take action. The \\\"Action Deck\\\" shows you the work that's ready to go. A PO that needs signing. A refund claim ready to file. You review the work, hit [Approve], and the system executes it. ✓ Ordering System: \\\"I found the best price. Ready to order?\\\" ✓ Claims System: \\\"I found 14 lost packages. File for refund?\\\" ✓ Simulation: \\\"If we wait, we lose $8.5k in sales.\\\" 3. System Posture Center Sleep At Night. You can't trust automation if it breaks every time something changes. The Readiness Scoreboard gives you peace of mind. It checks your infrastructure on demand. If a connection gets slow or data looks weird, it flags it immediately. You can verify system health whenever you need to ensure stability. ✓ Incident Timeline: See what happened and why. ✓ Scoreboard: A simple grade for your system's health. ✓ Auto-Fix: It suggests fixes for technical problems. 4. Hypothesis Lab Test The Future. Making big changes is scary. Runink removes the fear by letting you simulate the future. \\\"If we raise prices 5%, do we lose customers?\\\" The decision engine checks your history and tells you the likely outcome. Know the result before you make the move. ✓ See The Impact: \\\"Margin up 4%, Volume down 8%.\\\" ✓ Confidence Meter: Know how sure the model is. ✓ Make It Real: Turn a good idea into a rule instantly. Trust Architecture You're always in control.\n1. Shadow Mode Test safely. Runink watches your data and simulates actions without doing them. See exactly what the automated systems would have done (e.g., \\\"I would have filed this claim\\\") before you give them the keys.\n2. Graduated Autonomy You set the leash. Start with \\\"Junior Analyst Mode\\\" (System drafts, you approve). Graduate to \\\"Co-Pilot\\\" (System handles small tasks). Finally, unlock \\\"Full Autonomy\\\" only when you're ready.\nSuture The Bleeding. Direct answers to your most expensive problems.\nMy team follows SOPs loosely. How does this help? It\u0026rsquo;s hard to remember every rule in a fast-paced environment. Rules Studio turns your written SOPs into active \u0026lsquo;Guardrails.\u0026rsquo; It catches common slips—like duplicate POs—in real-time, helping your team stay compliant without slowing them down. Do I have to rip out my WMS or ERP? No. Runink is designed to work with your current stack, not replace it. We connect to your existing tools (Shopify, Guidewire, Snowflake) to catch the signals they miss. How long until I see a return on investment? Very quickly. Our initial \u0026lsquo;Leakage Audit\u0026rsquo; often identifies enough unrecovered claims and stuck shipments to cover the platform cost within the first few days. We focus on finding value immediately. Is this safe? Can automation break things? Safety is the priority. We start in \u0026lsquo;Shadow Mode\u0026rsquo; (simulation only). You see exactly what the system would do without it touching a thing. You only switch to \u0026lsquo;Action Mode\u0026rsquo; when you are fully comfortable with the results. Does Rules Studio require coding? No. It uses an automated editor to write the rules for you. You describe what you want (\u0026lsquo;Alert me if margins drop below 10%\u0026rsquo;), and the system builds it. Can the Operations Actionable Twins execute actual work? Yes. It connects to your systems to do the job. Every action (PO creation, Claim filing) is logged so you can see exactly who did what and when. Stop The Bleeding. See your operational risks in real-time and fix them automatically.\nGet Started \u0026rarr; "
